{{see|posé}}

==English==
=== Etymology ===
French ''[[poser]]'', from Vulgar Latin ''[[pausare]]'', influenced by Latin ''[[ponere]]''

===Transitive verb===
'''pose''' ([[posing]] [[posed]])
# set in place, arrange
# ask, set (a test or quiz)

===Intransitive verb===
'''pose''' ([[posing]] [[posed]])
# assume or maintain a pose

===Noun===
'''pose''' ([[poses]])
# position, arrangement (especially of the human body)
# affectation

===Adjective===
'''[[posable]]'''
# able to be posed

===Related terms===
* [[dispose]]
* [[suppose]]
* [[superpose]]
* [[impose]]
* [[expose]]
* [[propose]]
* [[prepose]]

